Regress actual_length on estimated_length and confirm your visual assessment of which points are influential or non-influential outliers based on Cooks distance. You can get a useful plot of Cooks distance by passing argument which = 4 to autoplot(). Or try the base R plot() function for comparison [e.g.plot(model)]!
